data.content:

&lt;p&gt;Since &lt;a href=&quot;http://php.net/regex&quot; rel=&quot;noreferrer&quot;&gt;POSIX regular expressions (ereg)&lt;/a&gt; are deprecated since PHP 5.3.0, I&apos;d like to know an easy way to convert the old expressions to &lt;a href=&quot;http://php.net/pcre&quot; rel=&quot;noreferrer&quot;&gt;PCRE (Perl Compatible Regular Expressions) (preg)&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Per example, I have this regular expression:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-php s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-php&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_ invoke__&quot;&gt;eregi&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&apos;^hello world&apos;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;How can I translate expressions into &lt;code&gt;preg_match&lt;/code&gt; compatible expressions?&lt;/p&gt;
